  "text": "Gene Ontology (GO)-based functional enrichment analysis is used to measure gene enrichment in annotation terms for the inter-individual variable genes. The significance score in Table 1 is -log (EASE Score), where the EASE Score is a modified Fisher exact p value [CITATION_1] obtained by DAVID. The GO terms passed the criteria, EASE Score ,0.1, and at least 2 genes in each GO term are considered for further comparison. Only 11 mutual GO terms exist for all selection criteria, and these are shown in Table 2 .",
